<p><b>How to communicate effectively with others pdf?</b> For real communication to occur, the verbal and nonverbal expressions must agree. What is said must be consistent with facial expressions, posture, and tone of voice to communicate effectively. Try to appreciate the emotion behind the words (vocal and visual messages) more than the literal meaning of the words.</p>
